An {@code invokedynamic} instruction linked to a {@code CallSite} delegates all calls to the site's current target

A {@code CallSite} is a holder for a variable {@link MethodHandle}, which is called its {@code target}. An {@code invokedynamic} instruction linked to a {@code CallSite} delegates all calls to the site's current target. A {@code CallSite} may be associated with several {@code invokedynamic} instructions, or it may be "free floating", associated with none. In any case, it may be invoked through an associated method handle called its {@linkplain dynamicInvoker dynamic invoker}.
